main event: Three different UFO sightings were reported by a civilian observer in Tampa, Florida in 1966.
interesting points: The first sighting involved six chrome or silver objects the size of four headlights, hovering about 50 feet above the ground for 5-10 minutes before disappearing.
The second sighting was of an object the size and shape of a Volkswagen car, covered in a white substance and moving in a 'wavering' motion before disappearing over the horizon.
The third sighting was of 12 four-pointed, 6-12 inch diameter objects that looked like small, white swirling clouds with lights, moving in a straight line over the treetops.
The observer had previously reported seeing UFOs while living in Michigan from 1957-1959.
The Air Force concluded the observer likely imagined or misinterpreted the sightings due to poor eyesight, as no other witnesses reported the same objects.
sighted object: Variety of UFOs including chrome/silver objects, a Volkswagen-sized object, and 12 four-pointed cloud-like objects with lights
